gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
Contains metadata and quality information on the Australian Regional GPS Network (ARGN), the South Pacific Regional GPS Network (SPRGN) and other permanent GPS stations across Australia, which are observed on a non continuous basis.
Metadata information for each tracking stations contains data such as the site name, connection type, location, position, equipment and their serial numbers, main contact agencies, etc.
The site quality database contains statistical quantities for each site for each day of year.

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
the alpha GeoServer PIRSA MinOcc is up on auscope-portal-test.
GeoServer does not need the version or xmlns options; these are included in the URLs below to show compatibility with the URLs used to access deegree. You may like to append &maxfeatures=10 if your browser cannot handle large XML responses.
The useful feature types:
mo:Commodity http://auscope-services-test.arrc.csiro.au/pirsa-minocc/wfs?service=WFS&request=GetFeature&version=1.1.0&typename=mo:Commodity&namespace=xmlns(mo=urn:cgi:xmlns:GGIC:MineralOccurrence:1.0)
mo:MineralOccurrence http://auscope-services-test.arrc.csiro.au/pirsa-minocc/wfs?service=WFS&request=GetFeature&version=1.1.0&typename=mo:MineralOccurrence&namespace=xmlns(mo=urn:cgi:xmlns:GGIC:MineralOccurrence:1.0)
gsml:MappedFeature http://auscope-services-test.arrc.csiro.au/pirsa-minocc/wfs?service=WFS&request=GetFeature&version=1.1.0&typename=gsml:MappedFeature&namespace=xmlns(gsml=urn:cgi:xmlns:CGI:GeoSciML:2.0)
gsml:MappedFeature is nested by feature chaining as a property of mo:MineralOccurrence.
Note that mo:Commodity/commodityGroup is not encoded as some values are null. Plenty of other properties are missing in these features (this is an alpha), but those supported should be sufficient for a minimal demonstration through the portal.

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
The Australian Regional GPS Network (ARGN) consists of a network of permanent geodetic quality GPS receivers, on geologically stable marks, in Australia and its Territories, with eight stations within Australia known as the Australian Fiducial Network (AFN).
These sites provide the geodetic framework for the spatial data infrastructure in Australia and its territories. They also provide input for the measurement of earth processes, such as crustal dynamics and sea level rise. Data from the ARGN network also contributes to the International GPS Service.
